,Not Recommended,246620,13135396,"Posted: 28 November, 2014",all,Whalerguy,"The fact that I like this game shouldn't detract from the fact that I can't recommend it.This is a game meant to be played on a phone, and it shows.  It is very one-dimensional and once you've figured it out (should take about 15 minutes at most) that's it.  Sure there are levels and things to unlock, but the bottom line is that it should only be purchased on sale.  I paid full price and I regret it.The rundown:-Fun, but the same way a single level of mario is.  You can do it a few different ways and win.  You can unlock things and play it again (in the same way) and win.  Satisfying the first three times and not much more.-Educating, but not in a good or useful way.  It gives legitimate details about pathogens but nothing else.  Like reading the cliffnotes of ""all about disease""-Entertaining in exactly the same way smallpox was, take that as you will.-Replayability is hugely limited due to the limited nature of the game.I'll admit to enjoying it the first two times through the rest of it wasn't so enjoyable.  I know I only show a few hours of the game but that's all it takes.  There's a basic strategy that takes you though twenty minutes of playtime and that's it.  Buy it on sale and enjoy it but NEVER pay full price or you'll be left with the knowledge that you did nothing but pay for an undergrad to fail his midterms."
