76561197978600652,Not Recommended,246620,21310744,"Posted: 18 February, 2016",all,Hyomoto,"This is a difficult review, I'm really struggling against the simple 'recommend/don't recommend' system here.  I don't think the game is bad at all, like many people I originally played this game on my cellphone and found it quite entertaining.  The whole game is here and I really have nothing against it or it's strategy.  Heck, it's one of the few mobile games I liked because it actually fit the medium it was made for.  And yet, that's the core of why I cannot recommend it: The game was better on mobile.This experience is tailored for a small touch screen.  The point and click gameplay was fast and fluid on a tiny screen but clunky on my HD display.  The interaction with your virus was a detached experience on a small screen as you played the observer tinkering with the virus' evolution.  The 'pimple popping' gameplay made sense as a way to pass time as you watched your virus spread.  On the big screen?  It almost comes off as insulting.  The simple evolution of your virus makes sense when you have ten minutes to play, but it feels empty at my desk.  Perhaps because I knew it as a time-wasting mobile game that I don't want it on my desktop but here we are and I really just don't.  I hoped that they'd make use of the big screen somehow, maybe take some risks and update the game.  I did not find that to be the case.Honestly I'm not recommending not buying it, I just don't think it's a good desktop PC game.  It barely surpasses it's flash roots.  And since you ~can~ play it on a cellphone or tablet, well, this may not be the worst port of a cellphone game to the PC but at the same time it's hardly better for it.  The pick up and play is gone.  The swift menu navigation is gone.  And I don't remember this on mobile, but an endless flood of tutorial messages drags things down further.  It's good for a few minutes of your time but do you really what to boot up your computer, log into Steam and kill ten minutes?  Maybe it is.  To me, all the gameplay which made it fit the mobile genre feels wasted and for ten dollars you could easily buy something far more interesting."
