76561198035627093,Recommended,246620,13462370,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,Oboemeister,"It's easy to look at a game like this, one that you played a few times on your phone, and say ""Oh boy another horrible mobile to PC port."" Well I can confidently tell you that that is not the case.General Pros:~ Easibly navigable GUI and map screen~ Detailed explanations of the implications of your in-game actions~ Random events that can help or hinder your plauges growth~ Fun upgrade paths that are exciting to explore and discover~ Multiple plauge types each with their own special abilities and upgrade pathsThe real question, however, is 'why should i buy this game on my PC if i already payed 5 bucks for it on my phone'?PC Pros:~ 3 all new plauge types that are very different from the generic plauges of the phone game (A zombie plauge, A Planet of the Apes Plauge, and a Plauge that allows you to partially control the infected!)~ Better controls, A 0prettier and more easily navigated GUI, and the ability to go 3X speed (The Phone only has 2X)~ Hundreds of awesome user made scenarios that allow you to plauge the world with everything from Evil Ninjas, to Cults of Cthulu Worshipers~ EXTREMELY easy to use Modding system (included with the game) that allows you to edit virtually every aspect of the game~ An Indev (in Development) multiplayer version.The cons to this game are minimal. While the core of the game remains constant with each new disease you play as, the depth, story, and gameplay can change greatly with different scenarios, mods, and disease types.If you can try to pick this game up on sale, after having spent $5 on the game for my phone i didnt really want to pay full price again, but on the same token i would snatch this game up while its still in the early access stage, because for the content it has and will have i would definitly want to get it before the price goes up."
