,Recommended,246620,26431502,"Posted: 5 November, 2016",all,TheFancyRoman,"Plague Inc. I remember playing it on my phone and tablet a year or two ago. It was fun. Now it is on Steam. And by now I mean it has been there for 10 months.The game costs 15 euros but it is free on mobile. Is it worth it? It makes me think about Fruit Ninja Kinect. Is it worth it? Well... do you want to play it on PC? Are you a streamer or a Youtuber? Did you get it from the Plague Inc boardgame for free? Then yes.Alot hasn't changed from the orginal game. Sure, it looks alot better. Not just graphics vice, but it overall feels more PC. It isn't just a game slapped on PC with the developer saying ""GIVE ME MONEY. But does it have 15€ worth of improvements? Lets see how the game works first:You start off by selecting a disease. When you win with that disease on normal or above, you unlock the next disease. Each one has its unique play style but they all basically work the same. Once you have selected your disease, you can move on to choose your starting country. WHY IS ALASKA PART OF CANADA? Once you have chosen a country, the game begins. You can upgrade your disease by giving it more killing power, more infectivity or making people think it is dangeous. Your disease then speads over the world etiher by land, boat or plane. Once people start dying and see ""Hey, theres this new disease going around! Lets deal with it!"".Now there will be a country that will be the main or the head of the research that tries to find a cure to your disease. The more damage you do, the more they invest in research. They can also block you from entering a nation and infecting it by closing the borders or executing the infected. There are many ways they can block you but a disease always finds a way, like infecting via birds, rodents, bats, water, air or livestock. They send these planes to get DNA or something, burst their bubble and kill each and every last one of them!. One match can easily last 30 minutes and its really fun.Thats the game in a nutshell. Theres also this very unique mode, the... the disease from The Rise of the Planet of the Apes. That SImean flu thing. It is very fun, you should check it out. Infecting apes and humans. It is a bucket of fun.But back to the main issue, is it worth 15 euros? Well you can go to the leaderboards or make your own custom scenarios, speed runs, CO-OP? This game has Co-Op!? Unfortunately I have no friends who own this game, so I can't really talk about it. Is it wort 15 euros though?I wouldn't say so. I have to say that this game isn't an game you will play actively. It is a phone game. It is a fun distraction, it is a game designed to be played while waiting for the buss or when you nothing to do. Despite all these new updates, it isn't worth 15 euros to me. Maybe to you. But I recommend you buy it on sale, like I did. I got it for 7,50. I think it was barely worth 7,50. 5 euros? Must buy. 7,50? Eh, I mean it is a fun little game to play. So I think I will give it a pass."
