76561198015907664,Recommended,246620,9499976,"Posted: 16 March, 2014",all,Baalzebul,"I am obviously not very good at this game because I have only unlocked 2 levels so far, viruses and fungi. (along with bacteria, which is what you start with to infect the world and wipe out the human race), but this game is a lot deeper than it first appears.  In a way, it's kind of like Risk, in the sense that you essentially need to infect (capture) each state on the map, and then wipe out the humans before they have time and resources to fight back, but the challenge is that unless you do things just right, a well laid plan can backfire pretty easily.Having said that, I've already dumped a good 20 hours into the game so far, and it keeps me coming back for more.  You get to know when you've blown it and have to do the game over after a few raounds of play, but eventually you figure out what strategy you need to do to win with the particular plague you are given.  At least partly.  There are enough randome elements thrown in such as unexpected mutations, unexpected actions such as the pesky humans putting filters in aircraft which can hinder your ability to spread.  Getting to the islands of Greenland and New Zealand (among several others) can make or break a game.  If there are ANY humans left alive at the end, you lose, full stop.But I would say this game is very well thought out (and appearenly a hit in it's previous mobile form) and even though it's not finished it's one of those games that just keeps yanking you back for more.  Just ONE more try, just one more round, and to me, that's when you are getting your money's worth in a strategy game.If you like risk, chess, or any world domination type game, this is definitely one to check out.  One warning, it's not finished yet, so there are still features like custom scenarios coming.  But don't worry, you have to get through multiple plagues to unlock all of them, and then you have to actually beat the game about 10 more times to unlock all of the buffs that you can get for your plagues at the start of each game.I don't know about anyone else, but I look foward to playing a few rounds each night.  Yes, I have lost sleep over this, and that's a sign of a great game!"
