,Recommended,246620,10639131,"Posted: 21 June, 2014",all,Walrus,"Create a plague and infect the world - pretty much as it says on the tin.A typical playthrough of this may take about 20 minutes. You create your plague (choosing from bacteria, virus, fungal infection and various others - most need to be unlocked through gameplay), choose a starting point and try to paint the map red essentially.You evolve your disease with traits and perks which determine its strengths and weakness (how contagious it is, how well it can spread overseas, which climates it is most effective in etc) and the goal is to wipe out the entire human race - nothing else is acceptable. There will be times when those bloody secluded Greenlanders or New Zealandfolk simply seem to refuse to get infected, and nothing is more frustrating, but when you get it just right, and watch it spread like absolute wildfire...very satisfying. Also, as someone who works in retail, destroying the human race is usually the ideal way to blow off steam after a hard day of work.I should mention this game started off as a smartphone app and has been ported to PC. The PC version is still being developed, but on the phone it is more or less the same exact game. Perfect for a bus/train journey or so."
