,Recommended,246620,28258676,"Posted: 8 December, 2016",all,Mr. Jackpots,"Interesting game!Plague Inc. Evolved is a really sick idea that has the potential to be an interesting strategy game. I'm really not into the bubble clicking thing but this can be removed later in the game: I still feel this may turn off more ""serious"" strategy gamers with it's free mobile app feel and that really I don't think that it adds anything in terms of game-play: I suspect it's there to add a sense of urgency and to keep the player's attention focused, but I really think that it would be better replaced with something that feels a bit less cheap.That being said, there's clearly a lot of depth here. The game ramps up the difficulty pretty quickly and there are a good few options for altering the core game pretty significantly.I've not felt particularly interested in sustained gameplay: it hasn't totally grabbed me in all honesty. Personally I find that the fact you can play through a single player game in a half hour or less very appealing. I recommend the game on this basis, that it's a good quick strategy fix. I'll be putting more hours into thisBut it's pretty unique as far as I can tell and it's a worthwhile addition to any strategy gamer's collection.EDIT:I've noted the comments below and edited this review accordingly: further proof that you should probably research something before low-rating.I do stand by my original comment that it still feels like a free-to-play game, albiet it a very nicely presented and polished one. My main gripe was the bubble clicking thing and since that is something you can get around I've changed my recommendation. I still think it needs to be removed for the reasons stated above."
