76561197972526943,Recommended,246620,24566619,"Posted: 27 July, 2016",all,Subtiliter,"The most morbid RTS I have yet seen. An RTS where you cannot command units. You are a disease. You are fighting against a simulation of disease response by human organizations. Your goal is to kill all humans before being cured. Your methods are choosing Transmision vector, Symptoms, and resistance to climate/drugs/research mutations. The choice of when to mutate how is interesting and fun to experiment with as you interact with the simulated global population. Expect to lose often as you feel out how the game responds to stimuli. Games can be very short, and there's a mild clicker aspect to keep you engaged in what would otherwise be a very hands off game. Pause often to keep up with clicking things and to spend mutation points at precise times.This game's mobile origins show, but its enjoyable enough to spend a few hours on trying to wipe out humanity."
,Recommended,246620,23767400,"Posted: 24 June, 2016",all,17 Crimes,"Plague Inc: Evolved is an exciting strategy game with many methods and difficulties. There is no single ""correct"" way to become a life-hating disease dictator, allowing you to try a variety of new scenarios and approaches for each of ten disease types. At higher difficulties, random events can make or break your entire evolutionary course, though not without cause or justification.Despite the difficulty of certain viruses (mainly the Necroavirus, in my case), I never felt the urge to look up a walkthrough. The game never got frustrating or repetitive, no matter how many times I clicked retry. Each time, I simply had to think harder and try new paths.Being a science type, I love the non-frustrating complexity that comes into play in this game. There are so many different things to try in terms of symptoms, transmissions, and now scenarios. Even after you've completed each disease, there's so much more to do. Highly reccomend it."
