,Recommended,246620,9582274,"Posted: 21 March, 2014",all,Lauren Jamilah,"I really love this game. I'm going to be going to school for infectious diseases so I'm kind of biased when it comes to this genre but I really do believe others will find it as fun as I do. This version is a lot more complex than the free online Flash game (I'm not sure whether or not it's made by the same people though) that has the same concept. If you liked the Flash version then you'll love this. The Flash one, however, get's kind of boring once you've beaten it the first time but Plague Inc: Evolved allows you to unlock items and options that increase the depth of your gameplay. By doing this, even after you've killed all of humanity once, there is still tons left in the game for players to want to come back to. Unlike the Flash version, you won't get bored after your first time winning as there will still be so much more to expreience. Instead of giving you all the options right at the beginning like the Flash version, you actually have to work for things in Plague Inc: Evolved. So far I've played around 36 minutes, which on the Flash version would have been long enough for me to beat the entire game, but with Plague Inc: Evolved 36 minutes is only enough to expreience the very beginning. I think one of the other really important features of this game is that, although you don't need to have a high end PC to play it on its highest settings, it still looks beautiful. If this is the kind of game you're into (puzzle, statagey, infetious diseases) or you enjoyed the online Flash version then I highly recommend buying Plague Inc: Evolved... you won't be disappointed. It's well worth the $15."
