76561198025202506,Not Recommended,246620,11468746,"Posted: 29 July, 2014",all,The Govern-mint,"I'm not entirely sure where to start when I write a review for this. The concept dates back to 2008, maybe earlier. This is by far the most refined version out there. At the time I am writing this, the 8th disease type, the Simian Flu, has just been released. The game is very nice, but unfortunatly lacks a lot of replayability. Because of this, many of the reviews you see, the reviewer only has 5-25 hours on the game. For all the other games you could get for $15, this one is tempting, but not the best thing. A good comparison, as far as game time, is CS:GO. People put hundreds upon hundreds of hours into that game. Some will even have hours in the thousands. You can simply get a game that will give you more hours of enjoyment other than Plague Inc. That being said, Plague Inc. has potential that has so far been realised. But charging $15 for it seems a bit overcharge for 5-25 hours of gametime. You are, however, getting exactly what you're planning on receiving if you decide to buy this game. If you can spare the money, go for it. If you're at a cross between this and another $15 game that is popular, like The Forest or CS:GO, get those games instead."
