76561198021129174,Not Recommended,246620,30549357,Posted: 16 March,all,sixstringbrad,"This is more directed towards the devs but everyone should go ahead and read this. I'm unsure where to place my recommendation. I had fun playing the game but there are many problems that I think the devs should know about and work on to make this game a more pleasurable experience instead of such a frustrating ""bang your head against the wall"" game.First I'll just say that this game is a great concept and has many interesting prospects and is an interesting perspective on how dangerous viruses and even bacteria can be. Having said that, there is a great deal more that could have been incorperated and perhaps can be incorperated with add ons and updates. Also, the system set up for the game that deals with infection vs. human scientific research needs to be fixed or further developed...Here are my issues with it on a scientific and gaming perspective.1. Scientific research rates compared to the amount of death and mental manipulation that the plague is capable of; They are unrealistic and frustratingly so.Once humanity is aware of the disease and it is infecting everyone, as soon as I start unlocking symptoms that effect the brain, the research seems to pick up faster instead of slowing down, which does not make sense whatsoever. If the entire world is infected and the human brain is directly targeted by the virus (plague) shouldn't research speed slow waaaaay down to a slow crawl as a result, not pick up as if humanity had a sudden spurt of super intellect in desperation? I've made everyone basically incompitent to the point of retardation and somehow, science still keeps cruising by as if nothing happened with only a 10% cut down on research percentage and it crawls right back up in a matter of seconds. This is very frustrating and highly unsatisfying...to be so close to victory and be cut short by an unrealistic program/system...2. Infection rates during multiplayer co-op are painfully slower than they need to be.I can't tell you devs how many times I played the game on multiplayer, cover the rest of the world, lose my co-op partner, have only one country left, have all the transmission abilities, and the last country either dies faster than my disease can infect or my disease is cured before I can infect everyone in that one. last country because the people of that last country somehow have the immune defenses of a fricking God...Yet the rest of the world is infected on a normal level. Just doesn't make any practical sense. How can the last humans on Earth, with no defence against a disease that doesn't replicate in lab conditions, have such a resistance against the, concievably, most infectious disease known to man? Some things like this need to be fixed, otherwise many of us are going to be more frustrated and unsatisfied with the game and disenchanted as I've slowly become.3. There could be more interactivity. More charts and representations of your disease. It would be cool to see the side effects in real time on a 3D model. There are 3d models, but they are boring and uninteresting and are only there for cosmetics.4. Symptoms like sneezing and insomnia should not spread world wide panic like it does in-game.In reality we do nothing to route out the common cold. It is very infectious, causes many symptoms, is everywhere at any given time, but we don't obsessively look for a way to rid of it entirely. Only in the game of Plague Inc. does an infection like the common cold cause mass panic and a world wide search for a cure as if it were cancer...The way humans are in reality: If it isn't killing us at this minute, don't worry about it...(truth). There are some ""philosophical"" stand points that should perhaps be adressed...There are plenty of strategies and plenty of ways to play the game and I've unlocked all of the diseases, but it is so frustrating to continue playing the game after all of the abilities and diseases are unlocked. There is nothing to push for and I don't want to even open the program anymore in fear that I'll just♥♥♥♥♥♥myself off and I'll have to play a different game. But it does offer a glimpse into the terrifying world of infectious disease and pestilence.It isn't worth $14.00...it's more worth like $9.99 or less and I feel a bit foolish for getting drawn into it. But it is a decent game. I do expect a better quality game so I'm hoping enough of these sort of reviews can get to the devs and push them a little harder to do something about it without also making the game perhaps too easy and maybe I'm giving too harsh of a critique, but I have spoken to many Plague Inc. gamers and my biochemist friend who plays the game and we agree more than disagree about all four of these issues. I'm not saying ""make it easier"", I'm saying ""Fix these little things and the game will be PERFECT"" so we can ALL enjoy the game. This is not a difficult game, but there are some ""bull crap""-y parts of the system of the game that should be further refined."
