76561198088633556,Recommended,246620,11426293,"Posted: 26 July, 2014",all,Th@tEp1cGuy,"Man runs with scissors, 12 hospitalized 11/10BEST GAM EVRBETER DEN CODMMORPGFPS OPEN WORLD360 QUICK-NO-SCOPES FOR DAYZDONT THINK BUY NOWUpdated/Actual Review:I ""reviewed"" this game about 2 years ago and it's come so far that I realized that this game deserves an actual review. I had been hearing about the original Plague Inc game for years when I got this and for the price I was genuinely afraid that it was going to become repetitive and not worth it. Well ladies and gentlemen, I am here to say that I was gladly wrong(ish). Was the game worth it's price in early access, well that is up to the person who was reviewing it. It WAS repetitive and it DID get boring after a while back then (even though I still loved it) but I have no doubt in my mind that if you enjoy games like this you should absolutly buy this. Let's go through the list.Notice: DID and WAS (the game has since been updated and these comments are no longer relevant)Gameplay: When I first began playing I joked about how this was like flash games where you just click whatever you can to advance your goals but I was wrong. This is a strategy game based on how you direct your pathogen, when you reveal yourself and how you keep yourself from being revealed. You could also argue resource management (I've seen friends without DNA points just after being found) but this personally isn't a problem I've had. With the many different pathogens which all change up gameplay entirely, your job is to simply destroy the world...easy right? There are only two real stages to the game right? Infect everybody without being found out/ Panic and be found immediatly (or hate the world on nanobots and panic on necroa virus) and then kill everybody. It can easily be summed down in words but as I've said, you can't just click everything to win. You have to move your virus in just the right way (I prefer boats, easier to get at Madagascar and Greenland but mostly because I like boats) and make sure that it can spread in the countries it moves to. You can easily be found out in your first country (if you're a first timer) and dead before you even know it. This gameplay allows players to have a basic strategy game without the extreme amount of time and thought process required for games such as Civilization or Europa. It also allows for fast games so you can easily sit down and play a game of Plague Inc while you're waiting for something (just remember, any computer is a laptop if you're brave enough). Of course, saying this I need to say that it can be difficult for people to pick up at first. I don't mean it's difficult to understand the controls I just mean newcomers should start on easy and work their way up. I could easily continue but I do need space for the rest of the review, sorry. (9/10)Sound: The music is pretty good, kind of ominous but you kind of need that for a game about killing everyone. I think they got the music design right for a game like this, but this is a strategy game, while music is nice to listen to it isn't really that important. It is the kind of music that keeps your head in the game and that's all that really matters. The sound design is excellent, there's no lag on the sound design, the bubble popping noise makes me want to pop more bubbles, I almost feel sad when I play with cheats on and I don't pop any bubbles. (9.5/10)Graphics: The graphics are good, I don't really see what they could do better. The world feels alive, that's all I can say. You really do begin to feel like you're killing the world and as you slowly watch as the world stops moving it really does feel empty (the world you've just destroyed you monster, not the graphics quality). There are real pictures for some of the countries (I wanted to say most but in truth I'm not sure) thanks to help the devs asked for from the community and the work had payed off tremendously. While some of the map of the world could be looked at to be made more realistic, for a 15/16 dollar game (sorry, don't know the U.S price) they hit the mark. (8/10)Workshop: This is important, I seriously felt the need to add this. The Steam workshop adds a whole new dynamic to this game. There's no longer just a set number of deceases, there's new ones being made all the time and while many games are starting to embrace the workshop, this one's been doing it for a while now and I must say, the community is just excellent.Multiplayer: (WILL REVIEW AT A LATE DATE MAYBE. #foreveralone)Overall: This game is just absolutly excellent and while I don't play it as much as I used to it has earned a place in my Steam Library and is definitely worth its base price. Mind you of course that you are paying extra in this version for better graphics, better sound and workshop support but it is so worth it that I would even recommend getting this if you have Plague Inc on your phone.Pros:-Fun for strategists-Great and well crafted music-Great Community-Lots of content-Good graphics-Easy to pick up, easy to put downCons:-Might get repetitive for some-Music repeats so if all you care about is the music (and you don't like what is being played) you won't enjoy the game-CDC deemed this game ""realistic"" (♥♥♥♥ EDUCATION)-Creates hate against Greenland (in the event of a deadly plague, go to Greenland)-Requires trial-and-error for newcomers-Makes me think of random ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t things to balence out the con section (ugh, work)"
