,Recommended,246620,9242348,"Posted: 23 February, 2014",all,Eaving,"The infectious gameplay of the mobile game hit has finally evolved the ability to commit cross-platform genocide. Being able to now play this game on PC is a boon to the gaming community in general. If you played this game on your Android device previously, you're going to adore this PC re-hash.Graphics have been enchanced significantly, and while you'd imagine that a game like Plague Inc wouldn't benefit from something like that, you'd be wrong. 3D models of pathogens, alongside a high-definition world map, have really enhanced the feel of the game. The gameplay remains intact, allowing previous players to easily adapt to the PC experience without taking something special away from the game we know and love.Unlike the mobile game, it seems that the PC version has no pay-to-win features and that is as it should be. $14 is a great price to pay for the ability to unlock all the features of the game during normal gamplay, and is a huge improvement over the mobile version. Basically, even if you have bought the game and spent money on it on your tablet or phone, buyit again on Steam. You shan't be dissapointed."
