76561198035805486,Not Recommended,246620,30717349,Posted: 24 March,all,efoxy06,"I am a huge fan of strategy games, especially strategy games with a twist like this.  I gave this one a shot, and it really just felt like an exercise in trial and error more than formulating a real strategy.  The tutorial teases you to watch news headlines, and read up on the geography of each region, hinting at a complicated and strategic gameplay with extreme attention to detail.  But in reality, the regions boil down to just ""arid or humid, hot or cold, densely populated or not.""  Throw in a wild card if they have an airport/seaport (dismissing that all countries do in real life...) and that's your variety.I had this one on the wishlist for a long time, and was swayed by all the positive reviews.  I just gave the reviews another glimpse to see if I was missing anything, and it feels like a majority of the positive reviews have less than 10 hours played.  Sorry, but if you actually enjoyed the game, you would find a reason to play it for more than 10 hours.  It usually takes me around 4-5 hours to dismiss a game in a genre like this, but I just can't find a reason to boot this game up and try it again.  Neat concept, bland execution."
