,Not Recommended,246620,32950677,Posted: 28 June,all,The British Wolf,"Don't buy it. Just don't. I'd always assumed this game would be good: Destroying the world via biological threats, it just always seemed fun. To an extent, it is. Like when you enslave the world using the Neurax worm or when your virus mutates ""sneezing"" just as mankind is about to die out (cos when your species is dead and your body is shutting down, having a cold is just salt in the wound). However, it's NOT fun. Which defeats the whole point of this game. It can't even be called a simulator either, because it's wildly unrealistic.Pray tell, how does mankind cure a disease which has changed its genome three times in a month, is resistant to all known drugs, is generally impossible to research and forces anyone infected to fall into a coma and die of total organ failure? And how exactly are you suppose to destroy the world with zombies, vampires or smart apes when, surprise surprise, mankind somehow has an army to the tune of 6 billion people? Because humans aren't THAT powerful, even with guns.I still can't beat the zombie virus, even on casual, even with GUIDES, because mankind (even the 10,000 I'd reduced them to) is still insanely overpowered to the point where I couldn't beat them even with ten times the amount of zombies and about 2/3s of their combat upgrades bought! Vampires? Useless. Apes? Put down so fast that Planet of The Apes doesn't exist according to my play through.Just don't buy this game. I got it on sale for like £5-£6 and I regret it because I couldn't bought one or two other games which would been more fun. So don't make my mistake, don't get suckered in by the idea of wiping out mankind, because this game takes all the fun out of every extinction scenario you can think of because it's completely unbalanced. The odds are always against the player and that doesn't make for a good time. So just go play the mobile version, it's free and gives you all the better parts of the game. Don't waste what little free cash you get on this hunk of junk."
