,Not Recommended,246620,10586339,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Rodd Noward,"I had high hopes for this game, as I loved the concept and MOST of the execution of the flash game, though not the flash game itself for reasons I will discuss shortly. I was hoping that this fixed the biggest issue I had with the flash game, but it appears not to have. My issue is simple: The game wants you to win the way the developers want you to win. That doesn't sound so bad, but experimentation is almost DISCOURAGED unless it's to find the way the developer wants you to win. That would be passable if the iteration time wasn't so LONG. Even on maximum speed, this is a SLOW game. It's ridiculous. Such a good concept, so bad in practice. If you get spotted, you're pretty much screwed too, unless you kill EVERYONE, because developing a cure is easy and screws you so hard that an industrial power drill made to drill through hardened steel couldn't do it faster.On top of that, to get ANYTHING done you need to beat the game several times. You unlock genes randomly, you unlock new pathogens in a linear fashion, proceeding from one to the next to the next... Winning is more about beating the system, rather than working with the system for a solution you like. The guides I've seen and my own experience is that the only way to win is to infect EVERYBODY undetected, then stockpile points until you've got a completely harmless pathogen turning into a disease more deadly than nuclear bombs fast enough to make Sonic blush.On top of that, they frontload you with NO information and don't even HAVE a tutorial beyond popups explaining SOME of the UI, just a ""How to Play"" hidden under the Escape menu with extremely unhelpful information.TL;DR: Iteration time too long, solutions MIGHT number more than 1 for any given pathogen (discounting minor differences), pathogen solutions nearly identical in approach, tutorial effectively non-existant, being cured is INSANELY easy and, to top it off, the majority of symptoms are only useful as paving stones to others. 2/5, at least it's not broken, but that's about all I like about the game itself."
