76561198004984602,Not Recommended,246620,12999238,"Posted: 18 November, 2014",all,Personal Miniature Equine,"I do not claim to be a strategist, but this game seems to be telling me that I'm not good enough for it. Players start the game with their only choices being bacteria or ""simian flu"", with none of the modifiers being available. I can't win on normal mode, and I like to have enough pride to avoid ""easy modes"". There is one way to win: kill every last human being on planet earth. Anything short of that, you lose, and gain nothing.""YOU GET NOTHING! YOU LOSE! GOOD DAY SIR!""While several tantalizing options such as mind-controlling ""Neurax worms"" and purpose-built biological weapons are available, I cannot access them because Madagascar, or New Zealand, or Greenland/Iceland close their only ports and ending 99% of human life is still as much of a loss as being eradicated within the first year. Modifiers can improve your plague out of the gate, but because one only unlocks them via winning, this becomes redundant.Before one of you decides that I'm just a loser, I'll compare this to another game based on difficulty, Dark Souls. Hypothetically, playing Plauge Incorporated would be like playing Dark Souls, but only if you didn't get to choose your class, you HAD to kill every boss, and when you died, you had to start from the beginning. I enjoy roguelikes, but those are USUALLY tests of skill and or getting ♥♥♥♥ed by the RNG. Plague Incorporated is actively attempting to prevent your success like nothing else I know of.The ideal strategy would be to infect everyone before they noticed and shut down everything, but random events including the ""mutations"" which give you a random boost to something serve to throw a wrench into your plans every time. ""Are you trying to be subtle? How's about your plague now makes people spontaneously combust!"" seems to be the norm.TL:DR  this game isn't enough fun to be worth smashing your head against the wall to unlock the fun."
