76561198039757882,Recommended,246620,9357358,"Posted: 5 March, 2014",all,Psyth,"Plague Inc. is not a highly complex game. It's a basic point and click with minimal UI options or perks. However, in sitting down to play it, I found it highly addictive. If you enjoy strategy and a good bit of reading, it's an excellent game. It takes a basic understanding of pathogens and a good bit of planning. Like chess, but with people and pathogens. As you complete scenarios you unlock different pathogens and genes to combine with them before starting your scenario. Once in game, the evolution process is fairly limited as far as evolution or upgrades. The game does have a few random events that accelerate or decelerate the spread or lethality of your creation which makes it interesting. The game AS IS, is really lacking, but still fun to play. Given how the Dev takes further development of the game, it has the potential to become extremely in depth. I definitely interested to see where things go. In the meantime, I'll be playing and trying to unlock all available mutations and genes. At $15 it's a little steep as far as what it is, but if you're a science buff / nerd / geek, in any sense of the word, it's still a must have. That being said, I see the true user base being limited, but for those that find the game appealing have great potential to become long term supports. I highly recommend watch an in-game video before purchasing."
