76561197968657460,Recommended,246620,9482416,"Posted: 14 March, 2014",all,Guernsey,"Watch my reviewhttp://youtu.be/_pIPxIbh910or read it belowBefore I start this review two big health warnings. This is an early access game and most of it is not complete. So don't expect a review, but my first impressions. Secondly Plague Inc is a tablet game on Apple and Android, I have only played the PC game.On the technical side, you don't need a powerful machine to run this game and don't worry about the tablet port side of things, the options menu is better than many full price games. Some things still need to be added like rebindable keys and accessibility options, but these things should be in the final release according to the Ndemic Creations website.So what is Plague Inc? It is a disease simulator, it lets you play anything from a humble bacteria to a full blown Zombie plague. You infect people, thwart human research efforts, spread across borders and kill people, lots and lots of people. Now this is fun in a dark kind of way, and the game does have lots of multiplayer and social media potential for competitive play. There is great replayability since the game is easy to pickup and yet there are many different strategies to employ. Still I can't give it an unequivocal recommendation for one reason, it does not make sense.Now I don't mean that zombies or brain worms don't exist, I don't have a problem of with that. It is the breaking of the laws of nature and common sense. How can everyone in the world be infected and never get better till a cure is found? Why do all the mutations in the game make the disease stronger?If you've ever studied biology you could go on and on about how odd the game model is, but from a gaming perspective it represents a lost opportunity for a really interesting simulation game. What you have instead is a fun, dark, casual, indie game.My verdict wait for the full game or a steam sale."
